{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UZFCxD9AyxsbZNCyzmWGvf","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F26 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC §7.5 (User Profiles — `/users`):\n6\t\n7\t- Profile page shows:\n8\t  - Identity cluster (user IDs + device IDs as chips)\n9\t  - First seen / Last seen\n10\t  - Event timeline: reverse chronological, same format as Explorer\n11\t\n12\tFrom SPEC §6.6 (`GET /api/users/[id]`):\n13\t\n14\t- Returns:\n15\t  ```json\n16\t  {\n17\t    \"resolved_id\": \"user@example.com\",\n18\t    \"first_seen\": \"...\",\n19\t    \"last_seen\": \"...\",\n20\t    \"identity_cluster\": {\n21\t      \"user_ids\": [\"user@example.com\"],\n22\t      \"device_ids\": [\"device-abc\", \"device-xyz\"]\n23\t    },\n24\t    \"events\": [...]\n25\t  }\n26\t  ```\n27\t\n28\tFrom SPEC §8 (Component Structure):\n29\t\n30\t- `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` — Profile page\n31\t- `src/components/UserTimeline.tsx` — component for user event timeline\n32\t\n33\t## Dependencies\n34\t\n35\tCompleted features this builds on:\n36\t\n37\t- **F14** (`GET /api/users/[id]` route) — `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts` serves the profile JSON; `src/lib/users.ts` exports `getUserProfile`, `UserProfile`, `IdentityCluster`\n38\t- **F18** (Navigation shell) — `src/components/Sidebar.tsx` provides layout\n39\t- **F21** (Shared UI components) — `src/components/ui/IdentityChip.tsx` and `src/components/ui/JsonChip.tsx`\n40\t- **F25** (User search page) — `src/app/users/page.tsx` links to `/users/[id]` via `IdentityChip`\n41\t\n42\tExisting files that will be imported or extended:\n43\t\n44\t- `src/lib/users.ts` — types `UserProfile`, `IdentityCluster`, `EventRow` (re-exported from `identity.ts`)\n45\t- `src/components/ui/IdentityChip.tsx` — renders resolved_id as clickable chip\n46\t- `src/components/ui/JsonChip.tsx` — renders collapsed JSON properties\n47\t- `src/components/EventTable.tsx` — existing event table component (reference for timeline format, but the profile timeline is a simpler non-paginated list, so a dedicated `UserTimeline` component is warranted per spec §8)\n48\t\n49\t## Files to create or modify\n50\t\n51\t- CREATE `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` — User profile page (client component fetching from `/api/users/[id]`)\n52\t- CREATE `src/components/UserTimeline.tsx` — Event timeline component for user profile (reverse chronological event list matching Explorer format)\n53\t- CREATE `src/components/users/useUserProfile.ts` — Custom hook for fetching user profile data from `/api/users/[id]`\n54\t- CREATE `src/components/users/__tests__/useUserProfile.test.ts` — Unit tests for the profile hook\n55\t\n56\t## Implementation order\n57\t\n58\t1. **Create `src/components/users/useUserProfile.ts`** — custom hook that:\n59\t   - Takes a `resolved_id` string parameter\n60\t   - Fetches from `/api/users/${encodeURIComponent(resolved_id)}`\n61\t   - Maintains state: `profile` (`UserProfile | null`), `loading` (boolean), `error` (string | null)\n62\t   - Fetches on mount and when `resolved_id` changes\n63\t   - Returns `{ profile, loading, error }`\n64\t\n65\t2. **Create `src/components/users/__tests__/useUserProfile.test.ts`** — unit tests for the hook\n66\t\n67\t3. **Create `src/components/UserTimeline.tsx`** — client component that:\n68\t   - Accepts `events: EventRow[]` prop\n69\t   - Renders an MUI `Table` with columns: Timestamp, Event Name, Properties (using `JsonChip`)\n70\t   - No Resolved Identity column (redundant on profile page — all events belong to the same user)\n71\t   - Reverse chronological order (events already sorted from API)\n72\t   - Empty state message when no events\n73\t   - `data-testid=\"user-timeline\"` on the table container\n74\t\n75\t4. **Create `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx`** — client component that:\n76\t   - Uses `useParams()` to get the `id` from the route\n77\t   - Calls `useUserProfile(id)` to fetch profile data\n78\t   - Displays loading skeleton while fetching\n79\t   - Shows 404 message if profile is null and not loading\n80\t   - Shows error message if fetch fails\n81\t   - Renders identity cluster section: user IDs and device IDs as MUI `Chip` components\n82\t   - Renders first seen / last seen as formatted dates\n83\t   - Renders `UserTimeline` with the profile's events\n84\t   - `data-testid=\"user-profile\"` on the container\n85\t   - `data-testid=\"identity-cluster\"` on the cluster section\n86\t\n87\t## Sprint contract\n88\t\n89\t- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits 0 with 0 failures\n90\t- [ ] Linter → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n91\t- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n92\t- [ ] Build → `pnpm build` exits 0\n93\t- [ ] File `src/components/users/useUserProfile.ts` exists and exports `useUserProfile`\n94\t- [ ] File `src/components/users/__tests__/useUserProfile.test.ts` exists\n95\t- [ ] File `src/components/UserTimeline.tsx` exists and exports `UserTimeline`\n96\t- [ ] File `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` exists and contains `\"use client\"`\n97\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/users/test` contains `data-testid=\"user-profile\"`\n98\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/users/test` contains `data-testid=\"identity-cluster\"`\n99\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/users/test` contains `data-testid=\"user-timeline\"`\n100\t\n101\t## Test plan\n102\t\n103\t- **Test file**: `src/components/users/__tests__/useUserProfile.test.ts`\n104\t- **Module under test**: `useUserProfile` from `@/components/users/useUserProfile`\n105\t- **Cases to cover**:\n106\t  - Fetches profile from `/api/users/{id}` on mount\n107\t  - Sets `loading` to `true` during fetch, `false` after completion\n108\t  - Populates `profile` with API response data on success\n109\t  - Sets `error` when API returns 404\n110\t  - Sets `error` when fetch fails (network error)\n111\t  - Re-fetches when `resolved_id` parameter changes\n112\t  - URL-encodes the resolved_id (e.g. `user@example.com` → `user%40example.com`)\n113\t\n114\t- **Integration gap**: HTTP checks for `GET /users/[id]` page rendering — requires dev server\n115\t- **Integration gap**: Identity cluster chips display with correct user_ids and device_ids — requires dev server and seeded data\n116\t- **Integration gap**: UserTimeline renders events in reverse chronological order — requires dev server and seeded data\n117\t\n118\t## Risks and open questions\n119\t\n120\tNone. The API (`GET /api/users/[id]`) is fully implemented in F14 and returns all needed fields (resolved_id, first_seen, last_seen, identity_cluster, events). The UI follows established patterns from the Explorer page (F20) and User search page (F25). Shared components (`IdentityChip`, `JsonChip`) are available from F21.\n121\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5987788-8a82-40d1-a82c-3ac604fd0766","uuid":"7d35d20f-fbff-4a15-bcee-774172327986","timestamp":"2026-04-15T17:26:58.576Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/features/F26-plan.md","content":"# F26 Plan\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\nFrom SPEC §7.5 (User Profiles — `/users`):\n\n- Profile page shows:\n  - Identity cluster (user IDs + device IDs as chips)\n  - First seen / Last seen\n  - Event timeline: reverse chronological, same format as Explorer\n\nFrom SPEC §6.6 (`GET /api/users/[id]`):\n\n- Returns:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"resolved_id\": \"user@example.com\",\n    \"first_seen\": \"...\",\n    \"last_seen\": \"...\",\n    \"identity_cluster\": {\n      \"user_ids\": [\"user@example.com\"],\n      \"device_ids\": [\"device-abc\", \"device-xyz\"]\n    },\n    \"events\": [...]\n  }\n  ```\n\nFrom SPEC §8 (Component Structure):\n\n- `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` — Profile page\n- `src/components/UserTimeline.tsx` — component for user event timeline\n\n## Dependencies\n\nCompleted features this builds on:\n\n- **F14** (`GET /api/users/[id]` route) — `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts` serves the profile JSON; `src/lib/users.ts` exports `getUserProfile`, `UserProfile`, `IdentityCluster`\n- **F18** (Navigation shell) — `src/components/Sidebar.tsx` provides layout\n- **F21** (Shared UI components) — `src/components/ui/IdentityChip.tsx` and `src/components/ui/JsonChip.tsx`\n- **F25** (User search page) — `src/app/users/page.tsx` links to `/users/[id]` via `IdentityChip`\n\nExisting files that will be imported or extended:\n\n- `src/lib/users.ts` — types `UserProfile`, `IdentityCluster`, `EventRow` (re-exported from `identity.ts`)\n- `src/components/ui/IdentityChip.tsx` — renders resolved_id as clickable chip\n- `src/components/ui/JsonChip.tsx` — renders collapsed JSON properties\n- `src/components/EventTable.tsx` — existing event table component (reference for timeline format, but the profile timeline is a simpler non-paginated list, so a dedicated `UserTimeline` component is warranted per spec §8)\n\n## Files to create or modify\n\n- CREATE `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` — User profile page (client component fetching from `/api/users/[id]`)\n- CREATE `src/components/UserTimeline.tsx` — Event timeline component for user profile (reverse chronological event list matching Explorer format)\n- CREATE `src/components/users/useUserProfile.ts` — Custom hook for fetching user profile data from `/api/users/[id]`\n- CREATE `src/components/users/__tests__/useUserProfile.test.ts` — Unit tests for the profile hook\n\n## Implementation order\n\n1. **Create `src/components/users/useUserProfile.ts`** — custom hook that:\n   - Takes a `resolved_id` string parameter\n   - Fetches from `/api/users/${encodeURIComponent(resolved_id)}`\n   - Maintains state: `profile` (`UserProfile | null`), `loading` (boolean), `error` (string | null)\n   - Fetches on mount and when `resolved_id` changes\n   - Returns `{ profile, loading, error }`\n\n2. **Create `src/components/users/__tests__/useUserProfile.test.ts`** — unit tests for the hook\n\n3. **Create `src/components/UserTimeline.tsx`** — client component that:\n   - Accepts `events: EventRow[]` prop\n   - Renders an MUI `Table` with columns: Timestamp, Event Name, Properties (using `JsonChip`)\n   - No Resolved Identity column (redundant on profile page — all events belong to the same user)\n   - Reverse chronological order (events already sorted from API)\n   - Empty state message when no events\n   - `data-testid=\"user-timeline\"` on the table container\n\n4. **Create `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx`** — client component that:\n   - Uses `useParams()` to get the `id` from the route\n   - Calls `useUserProfile(id)` to fetch profile data\n   - Displays loading skeleton while fetching\n   - Shows 404 message if profile is null and not loading\n   - Shows error message if fetch fails\n   - Renders identity cluster section: user IDs and device IDs as MUI `Chip` components\n   - Renders first seen / last seen as formatted dates\n   - Renders `UserTimeline` with the profile's events\n   - `data-testid=\"user-profile\"` on the container\n   - `data-testid=\"identity-cluster\"` on the cluster section\n\n## Sprint contract\n\n- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits 0 with 0 failures\n- [ ] Linter → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n- [ ] Build → `pnpm build` exits 0\n- [ ] File `src/components/users/useUserProfile.ts` exists and exports `useUserProfile`\n- [ ] File `src/components/users/__tests__/useUserProfile.test.ts` exists\n- [ ] File `src/components/UserTimeline.tsx` exists and exports `UserTimeline`\n- [ ] File `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` exists and contains `\"use client\"`\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/users/test` contains `data-testid=\"user-profile\"`\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/users/test` contains `data-testid=\"identity-cluster\"`\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/users/test` contains `data-testid=\"user-timeline\"`\n\n## Test plan\n\n- **Test file**: `src/components/users/__tests__/useUserProfile.test.ts`\n- **Module under test**: `useUserProfile` from `@/components/users/useUserProfile`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - Fetches profile from `/api/users/{id}` on mount\n  - Sets `loading` to `true` during fetch, `false` after completion\n  - Populates `profile` with API response data on success\n  - Sets `error` when API returns 404\n  - Sets `error` when fetch fails (network error)\n  - Re-fetches when `resolved_id` parameter changes\n  - URL-encodes the resolved_id (e.g. `user@example.com` → `user%40example.com`)\n\n- **Integration gap**: HTTP checks for `GET /users/[id]` page rendering — requires dev server\n- **Integration gap**: Identity cluster chips display with correct user_ids and device_ids — requires dev server and seeded data\n- **Integration gap**: UserTimeline renders events in reverse chronological order — requires dev server and seeded data\n\n## Risks and open questions\n\nNone. The API (`GET /api/users/[id]`) is fully implemented in F14 and returns all needed fields (resolved_id, first_seen, last_seen, identity_cluster, events). The UI follows established patterns from the Explorer page (F20) and User search page (F25). Shared components (`IdentityChip`, `JsonChip`) are available from F21.\n","numLines":121,"startLine":1,"totalLines":121}}}
