{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SDiULyKqm9145Z23db8kKe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tests are failing because the URL in the hook is a relative URL (`/api/users/...`) but `new URL()` requires an absolute URL. The tests in `useUserSearch.ts` use `new URL(\"/api/users\", window.location.origin)` to construct the URL so that `new URL(url)` works in tests.\n\nI need to fix the tests (or the hook) to handle relative URLs in tests. Looking at the `useUserSearch.ts` hook, it uses `window.location.origin` to build absolute URLs. But in the `useUserProfile` hook, I used a relative URL string directly.\n\n\nThe real issue is that my hook uses a relative path while the tests try to parse it as an absolute URL. I could either update the hook to construct absolute URLs like `useUserSearch` does, or modify the tests to validate the relative URL string directly instead of parsing it with `new URL()`.\n\nSince relative URLs are perfectly fine in a Next.js app, I'll fix the tests to use string matching for the pathname check rather than trying to parse the URL object.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1022,"cache_read_input_tokens":60157,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1022,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5987788-8a82-40d1-a82c-3ac604fd0766","uuid":"3171336c-262c-4fe2-832c-17d11eecc350"}
